On NBC’s Meet the Press, moderator Chuck Todd asked Pence about Trump’s policies to ban Muslims from entering the United States.
"Well, Hillary Clinton wants to increase Syrian refugees to this country by 550 percent," Pence said.
Syrian refugees by the numbersThe United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees is the international agency that tracks and promotes refugee resettlement around the world.
President Barack Obama agreed on behalf of the United States to accept 10,000 refugees for fiscal year 2016.
The UN has determined that about 478,000 Syrian refugees are in need of resettlement.